    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-09-13T13:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-09-13T13:36:00-05:00" n="284"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d284">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">412.00/125: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-09-13T12:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 13, 1920—noon</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received 5:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>392. The local press today publishes an Executive decree amending article 15 of
                    the Executive decree August 30, 1919 regarding claims<note n="67"
                        xml:id="d284fn67">
                        <ref target="frus1919v02#pg_640">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1919, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 640</ref>.</note> (Embassy’s despatch
                    number 2406 of September 17, 1919<note n="68" xml:id="d284fn68">Despatch not
                        printed.</note>) so as to admit claims for damages caused up to June 30th
                    1920 and to extend until February 5th 1921 the period in which such claims may
                    be presented.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
